{{Infobox language family |name=Basaa |ethnicity= |region= |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone A|Zone A.40]], reduced) |glotto=basa1283 |glottorefname=Basaa (A.40) }}
The '''Basaa languages''' are a clade of [[Bantu language]]s coded Zone A.40 in [[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages|Guthrie's classification]]. According to Nurse & Philippson (2003), the languages remaining from the formation of the [[Mbam languages|Mbam]] group form a valid node. They are: :[[Basaa language|Basaa]]–[[Kogo language|Kogo]] (Bakoko), [[Rombi language|Rombi]]–[[Bankon language|Bankon]]. [[Hijuk language|Hijuk]] was listed as unclassified A.50 in Guthrie, but according to ''Ethnologue'' it is quite similar to Basaa.
