'''''Daerpies Dierie''''' is a [[Southern Sami]] church [[quarterly]], founded in 1997 and headquartered in [[Snåsa]], [[Norway]].<ref>{{official website|http://www.samiskmenighet.no/event/dolink/famid/331840}}</ref> The magazine is financially supported by the [[Diocese of Härnösand]] in Sweden and the [[Diocese of Nidaros]] in Norway. The magazine's editor-in-chief and founder is [[Bierna Bientie]].<ref>{{cite web|title= Sámi Culture in the Nordic Countries – Administration, Support, Evaluation|url= http://www.utexas.edu/courses/sami/dieda/hist/nordic.htm|author=Gaski, Harald and Tr. John Weinstock|work= University of Texas |accessdate=27 June 2009}}</ref> Articles are published in [[Swedish language|Swedish]], [[Norwegian language|Norwegian]] or [[Southern Sami]]. The articles cover a wide range of topics, from Sami church life to more general news about the [[Sami people|Sami]] community.

