{{Infobox athlete | name = Eliška Drahotová | nickname = | fullname = Eliška Drahotová | image = | imagesize = | caption = | nationality = Czech | sport = [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]] | event = [[racewalking]], [[middle-distance running]], [[Steeplechase (athletics)|steeplechase]], [[cycling|cyclist]] | club = USK Praha, TJ Cykloprag | collegeteam = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1995|7|22}} | birth_place = [[Rumburk]], [[Czech Republic]] | residence = | coach= Ivo Piták | death_date = | death_place = | height = | weight = | pb = | country = {{CZE}} | medaltemplates= {{MedalCompetition|[[European Athletics Junior Championships]]}} {{MedalBronze|[[2013 European Athletics Junior Championships|2013 Rieti]]|[[2013 European Athletics Junior Championships#Women|10,000 m walk]]}} }}
'''Eliška Drahotová''' ({{IPA-cs|ˈɛliːʃka ˈdraɦotovaː}}; born 22 July 1995, [[Rumburk]], [[Czech Republic]]) is a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] [[Athletics (sport)|athletics]] competitor in [[racewalking]] and [[road cycling]], like her twin sister, [[Anežka Drahotová|Anežka]]. She won the bronze medal in the [[2013 European Athletics Junior Championships]], while her twin sister [[Anežka Drahotová]] took the gold.<ref name=rietiOfficial>{{cite web |title=Opening honours to the Drahotová twins |url=http://www.european-athletics.org/rieti-2013-news/12097-opening-honours-to-the-drahotova-twins.html |work=22nd European Athletics Junior Championships, Rieti/ITA, 18–21 July 2013 |publisher=European Athletics |accessdate=3 September 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130720010122/http://www.european-athletics.org/rieti-2013-news/12097-opening-honours-to-the-drahotova-twins.html |archivedate=20 July 2013 |df= }}</ref> Her global debut in cycling also came that year at the [[2013 UCI Road World Championships]]. There she placed 34th in the [[2013 UCI Road World Championships – Women's junior time trial|junior time trial]].
She also competes in the running events: half-marathon, 3000 m, 2000 m, 1500 m, 800m, as well as in on other racewalking distances, including the 20&nbsp;km walk.<ref name=all-athletics3September2013>{{cite web|title=Profile of Eliška DRAHOTOVÁ|url=http://www.all-athletics.com/en-us/athlete/329783|work=All-Athletics.com|publisher=Elite Ltd.|accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref>
