{{Infobox Union |name= SzEF |country= [[Hungary]] |affiliation= [[ETUC]] |members= 274,000 |full_name= Forum for the Cooperation of Trade Unions |native_name= Szakszervezetek Együttmöködési Fóruma |image= |founded= June, 1990 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Budapest]], Hungary |people= [[Endre Szabó]], president |website= [http://mathom.dura.hu/szef/ mathom.dura.hu/szef/] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Forum for the Cooperation of Trade Unions''' (SZEF) is a [[national trade union center]] in [[Hungary]]. With a membership of 274,000 the SZEF represents mainly white collar workers in education, social services and health care, cultural institutes and government agencies.
The SZEF is affiliated with the [[European Trade Union Confederation]]
