'''Maltese identity cards''' are issued to Maltese citizens and other lawful residents of Malta. They can be used as a [[travel document]] when visiting countries in the [[European Union]] and the [[European Economic Area]].

They can also be used instead of a [[Maltese passport]] to visit [[French overseas territories]], the [[Faroe Islands]], [[Greenland]] (''de facto''), [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]], [[Montserrat]] (for max. 14 days), [[Turkey]] and on organized tours to [[Jordan]] (through [[King Hussein International Airport|Aqaba Airport]])

