'''The Centre for Polish Studies''' (Centrum Kształcenia Języka Polskiego in Polish) is a [[Warsaw]]-based school of [[Polish language]]. The school organizes courses in Warsaw, [[Sopot]] and [[Cracow]]. It is a private institution established in 2000 by Anna Jurewicz-Sawa, a teacher of Polish as a foreign language.

The Centre for Polish Studies promotes itself as a school with a mission of popularizing [[Polish culture]] and language among foreigners. Their website reads: “Our mission is to help foreigners get to know not only Polish, but also [[Poland]]: we believe that language, although it is key to understanding a country and its people, is not enough – therefore, we also teach our students [[culture]], [[economy]] and [[history]] of Poland”.<ref>http://www.learnpolish.edu.pl</ref>

